Steps (Portal): Restrict Guest Invitations
==========================================
Go to Microsoft Entra Admin Center
Navigate to:
External Identities → External collaboration settings

Configure:

Guest invite settings → Only users assigned specific admin roles can invite guests

Allow only:

Global Administrator
User Administrator
Privileged Role Administrator


Steps (Portal): Enforce Access Reviews for B2B Users
====================================================
Go to: Identity Governance → Access Reviews

Create New access review
Scope: Users → Guest users

Reviewers: Self or resource owners

Configuration:

Recurrence: Quarterly / Monthly
Auto‑apply results: Enabled
If no response: Remove access
Require justification: Optional


Steps (Portal): Use Access Packages with Expiration
===================================================

Go to: Identity Governance → Entitlement Management → Access Packages

Create Access Package: Add Groups / Apps / SharePoint / Teams

Lifecycle:

Access expiration (e.g., 30 / 60 / 90 days)
Require approval
Automatically remove access on expiry


Optional: Automatic Cleanup of Inactive Guests
==============================================
Go to: Identity Governance → Lifecycle Workflows

Use built‑in template: Remove inactive guest users

Configure:

Condition: No sign‑in for 30–90 days
Action: Disable or delete user


Go to https://aka.ms/ge

Sign in with admin account
Set API version to v1.0
Click Modify permissions
Add and Consent to: Policy.ReadWrite.ConditionalAccess

Deploy via Graph

--> There is no JSON / Graph / Azure Policy that configures guest invitation restrictions.
--> For Access Reviews:
    POST https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/identity/conditionalAccess/policies
    JSON
--> For Expiring Access Packages
    POST https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/identityGovernance/entitlementManagement/accessPackages
    JSON
--> There is no JSON / Graph / Azure Policy for Automatic Cleanup of Inactive Guests.

